name: narrative-report-brigantine-national-wildlife-refuge-september-october-november-december-1-b5c9c
notes: This narrative report for Brigantine NWR outlines Refuge accomplishments from September through December of 1944. The report begins by summarizing the weather conditions and water conditions during this period. Wildlife- including migratory birds, upland game birds, big game animals, furbearers, raptors, and fish- is also covered. The Refuge development and maintenance section discusses physical developments, plantings, and collections and receipts. The public relations section of the report describes recreational uses, Refuge visitors, violations, and safety. N-R forms are attached.
